			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The pet/foci upgrades really only help the mage.  Again...it is a good start and definitly a good thing.  It doesn't really help make mages more group or raid desirable though.  
<br />

<br />
I think it can be safely said that no elemental level guild recruits mages for their DPS or their utility.  Due to Wizards and Rogues ability to dmg fire and magic resistant mobs, they make much more reliable DPS.  Utility wise, CoH and Mod rods do not make or break a raid anymore.  Those 2 raid abilities that people like to bring up as proofs of Mage utility need to be discarded as ancient history.
<br />

<br />
Elemental Draw is a good idea, but it doesn't go far enough.  2 things need to happen with this line of spells.  SoE took the safer route with this spell, in it's current form, it's less likely to be nerfed due to the built in anti-abuse  features.  However; it could be much more useful...
<br />

<br />
1) Needs to be made into an instant mana gain, much like pet canna used to be.  You are canna'ing your pet after all..why should an instant HP hit on your pet return a Mana over Time gain to you?
<br />

<br />
2) A group version also needs to be made and this one also needs to be an instant mana gain.
<br />

<br />
BTW...I'm saying Instant due to the buff slot issues on raids and well...people notice that instant hit better.  Kinda like when a SK uses their group mana tap spell.
<br />

<br />
A reason to have the MGB skill should also be developed for the raiding mage.  Perhaps a "Protection from the Elements" buff that raises MR, FR and CR for 1-2 minutes and provides some extra mana regen or extra 200 HP..something to help, yet allow it to stand out on it's own compared to the druid and BST MGB desired spells.  Maybe a group version of "Protection of Calliv"...that would also certainly help raids and make a raid want more then just a token Mage to say they have a mage.<br />_________________<br />Verser - 65th .49999 Elf Bard
<br />
Sleethr - 61st Dark Elf Mage
<br />
Medec - 61st Dorf Battle Cleric
<br />
Bertoxxolus: Order of the Scattered Winds</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
